<Author>tatitah
<Content>Okay, but bring your cell phone! I booked directly for my mother and my aunt who are senior citizens. Once they arrived, my mother wanted to make a phone call. The front desk claims that I said that I put a block (this is not true). Then they added that the guests are not allowed to use the phone. They claim that the guests do not pay up. My mother mentioned to them that she is willing to pay, but they insisted that she cannot make the calls. I have to call my mother. I believe this is crazy. Not everybody has a cell phone and this is first time I hear of this. Of all the experiences I had with hotels this is really surreal. Also, the room that they were in, the shower head looked like it is slightly hanging. Water spilled on the floor and my mother almost fell down. Luckily, my mother and my aunt went down to complain about it and their room was changed.Another thing was I booked for three days the room. The front desk mentioned it was for two days. My mother insisted, but they didn't budge. She had to pay for the extra day out of pocket. The front desk even tried to charge the extra day to my credit card without calling me. My mother luckily saw this and insisted on a hard copy of the statement.These were the issues that both my mother and aunt experienced. Otherwise, it it a nice hotel.My suggestion is definitely bring a cell phone. Also double check and make sure that you are reserving for a certain amount of days.Unfortunately if it was not because of these issues, things would have been better. 
