<Content>Luke warm- Pedregal Luke warm - Pedregal; is the way I feel, If you ask my wife she would tell you they where cold. I will start from getting there. First off, the motel gives you directions to the motel on their web site, but only from the town, since I was coming from Bayamon I had to look them up on MapQuest which only got me to the town and from there I figured out where they where from the motels directions. Once I arrived at around 4:30, I found that there where two wedding receptions at the motel. One of the reception halls is acroos the way from the rooms, and that proved challenging to try and sleep with the music so loud. Since, it was raining that day the floors and stairs that lead to the 2nd deck rooms where really slippery, so watch your step. On day 2 and 3, we had problems with no hot water to shower with in the mornings (this was eventually fixed each day). The motel sits in the middle of a community and is set up so it looks and feels like and oasis - they almost pulled it off except for when your at the pool you can see the projects right across the street. The motel is only 5 minutes from Crash Boat beach which is a plus. The staff gets an excellent grade for service and support. They go out of their way to help you and are very friendly- my hat goes off to them. The staffs support made up for some of the problems with the motel but not all. The resturant at the motel is not part of or run by the motel. The food was okay, and a bit pricy for the quality of the food. I'm critical of the food because I'm Puerto Rican and expected better. Overall it was okay for the price I paid. 
