<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>disappointed Recently I vacationed in Puerto Rico and was disappointed with the conditions of the hotel. I would like to advise hotel seekers that what's posted is not necessarily, what to expect. When I arrived at the hotel/motel, and approached the front desk the agreement was not what I agreed to pay. I had made my reservations via telephone and was quoted a different price for three nights. I was very disappointed to have been presented with this on a vacation. So for the sake of enjoying my vacation, I choose not to make a big deal about this, rather just post a message of what had happened. I then entered the room and the conditions of the motel were not at best, for the price I was paying. The following day, I had gone touring. Once I arrived back to the room, I walked into a huge puddle of water. I called the front desk, and informed them of the situation. The gentleman at the front desk came to clean the puddle of water and explained the water was leaking from the a/c. He explained the A/C can't be left on for a long period of time. It was very frustrating to have to deal with these issues and having to walk into a hot room. I am aware I was not at a top hotel, but I don't think this should have happened. This has no reflection on the personnel, rather the advertisment, conditions and management. For those who are seeking a place to stay for a vacation, be my guest and stay. But let this be a warning. Make sure you have in writing what you will pay and the penalties/information for cancelation. Keep in mind this is not a modern/ new conditioned hotel. Time has taken it's path through the hotel. 
